<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 5:14AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Bands of heavy snow showers this morning...
At 515 AM, bands of heavy snow showers continue to move from west
to east through the region.
The snow showers only last about 30 minutes as they move through,
but snowfall intensity can be heavy.
These snow showers can produce a quick one inch of snow
accumulations as they move through.
Most of the snow showers will begin to diminish after 9 AM.
Those traveling this morning should be alert for quickly changing
road conditions, along with areas of poor visibility.</description>
